node.text:
Factual Tuesday: Bloating

Bloating (distended stomach) is a normal occuring thing! I have now seen multiple "health coaches" saying it isnt, and its because your health is suffering from an unlimited amount of made up theories.

Bloating happens when the GI tract becomes filled with air or gas. This can be caused by something as simple as the food you eat or drink, some foods produce more gas than others, especially cabbage, caffeine, broccoli, beans, lentils etc. Other simple reasons for bloating are having your period, food intolerances, hormones, stress, overeating, inactivity, lack of sleep etc. Obviously there's a ton of reasons to why our midsection expands during the day, and its so perfectly normal that it does so, please dont get caught up in the "youre broken and needs to be fixed with my help" misleading online health coach bs.

Happy factual Tuesday

#healthiswealth #eathealthy #dontcompare #bloated #itsnatural

node.text:
A little reminder if you're trying to lose weight: Always look for something positive.

Only did half of your workout? Better than doing none of it. Ate 2 cookies? Better than eating 4 like you used to. Didn't lose any weight this week? Maybe your clothes fit better.

Your mental state has a big influence on your
physical state. Do your best and stop being so hard on yourself! We arent striving for perfection, we are striving for fun times and sustainability.

Ps. We are keeping Norr home from daycare for 3 weeks, and as you can see he's the big boss, mom are not allowed to pose for more than 30 secs at a time 🤣

#positiveenergy #strongmom #weightlossinspiration #healthyhabits

node.text:
What's the most non prioritized, yet one of the most important factors when it comes to our health?

Sleep is! Ongoing sleep deficiency, is linked to an increased risk of heart disease, kidney disease, high blood pressure, diabetes, and stroke. On a fitness/weight lifting level, sleep also plays a vital role too, with lack of sleep you wont make much progress since proper sleep aids in the following:

1. Energy to lift heavier and longer
2. Increased fat mobilization
3. Faster recovery and repair
4. Hormone release (the good one's)
5. Mental sharpness/alertness
6. Immune support

And many other important things as well.

So, make it a priority for the sake of your health, it's way more important than you might realize.

#sleeptime #healthyhabits #healthiswealth #strongwomen

node.text:
Not a before not an after

Picture 1 is posing vs how I actually look right now having my period, picture 2/3 is posing vs standing relaxed, picture 4 is outright posing unnaturally to make my attributes "pop".

It makes a huge difference how you pose, how the light hits you, what clothes you wear, what you ate yesterday, how you slept and so on.

Don't compare anyones feed to your own, because you are just as lovely, beautiful and amazingly unique as all those people you yourself think is exactly that.

Happy Thursday sweet peeps.

#instavsreality #believeinyourself #bodytransformation #perfectlyimperfect

node.text:
The fake fitfluencers makes a killing convincing people they are broken, that their metabolism isn't functioning, that they eat too little to lose weight (wtf), and is just missing what they can provide:

That ONE thing.
That ONE diet.
That ONE pill.
That ONE routine.
That ONE product.

But here's the truth: There isn't *ONE* thing, and you're NOT broken. You probably just need to lift, eat like an adult, move around more and be patient.

Happy Monday and week ahead gals and doods

#patience #lies #liftheavy #healthyhabits #itsalifestyle

Reklame

One of the hardest things you can do as a
woman is show up as your whole self, because we always gets judged upon our look's, body, glam and personality. The reason for that being, is people feel intimidated by women who are comfortable with who they are. Truth is that the more you that you become, the less chance there is of everyone liking you.

You have to remember that the goal isn't to have everyone liking you, the goal is to like yourself.

Happy Weekend.

#knowyourworth #believeinyourself #youareenough #standtall

node.text:
Adam Moserri

Is the CEO of Instagram, and he broke the news himself : Instagram is no longer a photosharing app.

So, forget growth of reach and engagement from now on, Instagram is turning into a video and shortclip competitor to TikTok, and in the future YouTube, by basicly giving people who wants to deliver a message via captions and beautiful images the middle finger.

Posting pictures, writing captions, being creative in front, and behind the camera, will no longer be "rewarded", so now you know why your reach, engagement and exposure have dropped dramatically the past few weeks. Of course there's more to it than this simplified caption, and if you didn't see the videolink by @thechrishau I posted in my stories yesterday, go checkout his video on YouTube where he goes into depth with what's up/down in all of this change Instagram is going through.

So, going forward from here is going to be a challenge, but a challenge is always welcoming, and threading new waters always brings new opportunies, so let's cheer to that, guess I have to make a lot more video material from now on.

Happy Tuesday

#movingon #moveon
#changes #embrace #believeinyourself
